# {{EXTENSION_NAME}}

An [Asyar](https://github.com/Xoshbin/asyar) theme extension.

## Getting started

Open `theme.json` and fill in the CSS variable values you want to override.
Variables left as empty strings are ignored — only the values you set are applied.

## Project structure

```
{{EXTENSION_ID}}/
├── manifest.json     — extension metadata
├── theme.json        — CSS variable overrides
└── fonts/            — optional custom fonts (.woff2, .ttf, .otf)
```

## Adding custom fonts

1. Create a `fonts/` directory and drop your font files in.
2. Declare them in `theme.json` under a `"fonts"` array:

```json
{
  "variables": {
    "--font-ui": "'My Font', sans-serif"
  },
  "fonts": [
    {
      "family": "My Font",
      "weight": "400",
      "style": "normal",
      "src": "fonts/MyFont-Regular.woff2"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Validate & publish

```bash
asyar validate    # check manifest.json and theme.json
asyar publish     # package, release on GitHub, and submit to the store
```
